---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Elite Project"
  description="Read the terms and conditions for using the Elite Project template."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top,_rgba(67,56,202,0.18),_transparent_60%)]"
    >
    </div>
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pb-24 pt-28">
      <p
        class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-slate-400"
      >
        Legal
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-5xl">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-base text-slate-300">
        Last updated: October 23, 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-slate-950/80 py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-12 px-6 text-slate-300">
      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
          1. Acceptance of Terms
        </h2>
        <p>
          By accessing and using the Elite Project template, you accept and
          agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree with
          any part of these terms, you may not use this template.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">2. License</h2>
        <p>
          Elite Project is provided as an open-source template. You are free to
          use, modify, and distribute this template for personal or commercial
          purposes, subject to the license terms included in the repository.
        </p>
        <p>
          Attribution is appreciated but not required. However, you may not
          claim original authorship of the Elite Project codebase itself.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">3. Use of Service</h2>
        <p>
          This template is provided as-is for building static websites. You are
          responsible for:
        </p>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
          <li>
            Ensuring your use complies with all applicable laws and regulations
          </li>
          <li>
            Securing any sensitive data you integrate into your deployment
          </li>
          <li>Maintaining and updating your deployed site</li>
          <li>
            Reviewing and accepting third-party service terms if you integrate
            them
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
          4. Disclaimer of Warranties
        </h2>
        <p>
          Elite Project is provided "AS IS" without warranty of any kind, either
          express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of
          merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or
          non-infringement.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not guarantee that the template will be error-free, secure, or
          suitable for your specific needs.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
          5. Limitation of Liability
        </h2>
        <p>
          In no event shall Elite Project or its contributors be liable for any
          indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages
          arising out of your use or inability to use the template.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
          6. Third-Party Services
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you integrate third-party services (analytics, CDNs, form
          processors, etc.) into your deployment, you are solely responsible for
          compliance with their terms of service. Elite Project is not
          affiliated with or responsible for any third-party services you choose
          to use.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">7. Modifications</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will
          be effective immediately upon posting to this page. Your continued use
          of the template after changes constitutes acceptance of the modified
          terms.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">8. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with
          applicable laws, without regard to conflict of law provisions.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us
          at
          <a
            href="mailto:hello@eliteproject.dev"
            class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
          >
            hello@eliteproject.dev
          </a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
